race.comment: EXTREME VIRTUE (5) should be at peak fitness here and will give a bold sight. Three runs this time in have been rock solid, trying hard but being held up when setting it up for those further back at Cranbourne. She draws ideally here and will be in front for a long way. WATERSPORTS (12) appreciated the step up to 1500m at Cranbourne with a determined win in this class, getting the verdict by a head. She can track the pace again here and make it a double. MOMETZ (10) didn't have the best of luck behind a smart one at Sandown Lakeside and looks ideally placed going to a mile on the big track now. OTAGO (4) was better last time in a bunched finish. His best would win this but he's had issues. HIS FINEST HOUR (11) tried hard here behind a well-ridden winner last start and has claims.
